Female (Red-winged).description: Female Red-winged Blackbirds are more heavily streaked overall compared to female Brown-headed Cowbirds. They also have a thinner bill.

Adult male.description: Brewer's Blackbirds are larger and have a thinner bill than Brown-headed Cowbirds, which have a short conical-shaped bill. Adult males have a yellow eye whereas Brown-headed Cowbirds have a dark eye.

Female.description: Brewer's Blackbirds are larger and have a thinner bill than Brown-headed Cowbirds, which have a short conical-shaped bill. Females have a darker throat compared to female Brown-headed Cowbirds.

Adult male.description: Common Grackles are larger, longer-tailed, and lankier than Brown-headed Cowbirds.
Bronzed Cowbirds can be separated from Brown-headed Cowbirds by their thicker neck and red eye.

Female.description: Female Bronzed Cowbirds have a red eye and a heavier bill compared to female Brown-headed Cowbirds, which have a dark eye and a less hefty bill.

Male.description: Male Shiny Cowbirds are uniformly colored while male Brown-headed Cowbirds have a brown head and black body.

Female.description: Female Shiny Cowbirds have little to no streaking on the belly while female Brown-headed Cowbirds are finely streaked below.
